'''Imre Fényes''' ({{IPA-hu|ˈimrɛ ˈfeːɲɛʃ|lang}}; 29 July 1917  - 13 November 1977) was a [[Hungarian people|Hungarian]] [[physicist]] who was the first to propose a [[stochastic interpretation]] of [[quantum mechanics]].

